Calendar Watchface for Pebble

This is a Watchface for the Pebble Watch.  It shows the current date and current time in the top half, and then a small calendar w/ 3 weeks: last, current, and next week, in the bottom half.

Near the top of Timely.c you will find the following #defines and flags for configuring the appearance of the calendar.

#define TIMELY_DARK:
        #defined  = Black text on White Background (default)
        undefined = White text on Black Background

#define START_OF_WEEK
        Offset days of week. Values can be between 0 and 6 
        0 = weeks start on Sunday
        1 = weeks start on Monday
        2 = weeks start on Tuesday 

grid:
        true  = Draws horizontal and vertical lines between the rows and columns (default)
        false = Does not draw said lines

invert
        true  = Todays date will be larger & bold and the Text & Background colors will be inverted (default)
        false = Todays date will be larger & bold

vibe_hour
        false = Do not vibrate at the top of the hour (default)
        true  = Vibrate at the top of the hour

daysOfWeek
        array that holds the text used for the column headings

        
        
        
